    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Ageratum panamense are its antimicrobial, anti-inflammatory, and antiviral activities. The plant's antimicrobial properties are attributed to flavonoids, such as quercetin, and saponins, which inhibit the growth of various microorganisms, including bacteria and fungi. Ageratum panamense has been found to possess anti-inflammatory properties, particularly due to the presence of volatile oils, like beta-pinene and beta-myrcene, which reduce inflammation and pain. Additionally, the plant's antiviral activity is attributed to flavonoids, such as kaempferol and isorhapontigenin, which inhibit the replication of certain viruses. The plant's antioxidant properties, which are also a result of the presence of flavonoids, protect against oxidative stress and cell damage.",
