    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Ageratum panamense are ageratum tea, infusion, tincture, salve, and decoction. Ageratum tea is made by steeping dried flowers in hot water to treat fever, cough, and inflammation. An infusion of Ageratum panamense flowers is used to treat digestive issues, such as diarrhea and dysentery. A tincture of the plant is prepared by soaking the flowers in a solvent like ethanol or glycerin to treat respiratory issues like bronchitis and asthma. A decoction of Ageratum panamense roots is used to treat arthritis and rheumatism, while a salve made from the plant is applied topically to treat wounds and skin irritations.",
