    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Ageratum panamense improperly are numerous and can be severe. Experiencing allergic reactions is a common side effect due to its toxic properties, which can lead to the development of skin irritation in some individuals. This skin irritation can range from mild redness to severe blistering and can be accompanied by other symptoms such as itching, swelling, and rashes. Ingesting the plant can also induce vomiting as the body attempts to expel the toxin, and in severe cases, it can lead to more serious health complications. If ingested in large quantities, Ageratum panamense can cause severe gastrointestinal distress, including nausea and vomiting, which can be life-threatening if not treated promptly.",
    "uses": "Ageratum panamense has been traditionally used in folk medicine for its potential anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties. It is often used to treat various health conditions, including fever, respiratory issues, and gastrointestinal problems. In some parts of the world, the plant is used to treat wounds, skin infections, and other minor health issues. However, more research is needed to confirm its effectiveness and potential side effects. The plant's medicinal uses are not well-studied, and its safety for human consumption has not been extensively documented.",
    "taxonomy": "Ageratum panamense is a species of flowering plant in the family Asteraceae, commonly known as the blue mist flower. It is native to Central America and is often grown as an ornamental plant due to its vibrant blue flowers and delicate foliage. The species is part of the genus Ageratum, which comprises approximately 30 species of flowering plants. Ageratum panamense is often used in tropical and subtropical garden designs, adding a pop of color and texture to the landscape. Its classification as a member of the Asteraceae family reflects its evolutionary relationships with other flowering plants in this group.",
    "benefits": "Ageratum panamense is known to have various health benefits, including anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties. It is used in traditional medicine to treat fever, cough, and respiratory issues. The plant is also believed to have antimicrobial properties, helping to prevent infections and promote wound healing. Additionally, Ageratum panamense is said to have anti-cancer properties, although further research is needed to confirm its effectiveness. Its health benefits are largely attributed to its rich content of flavonoids, saponins, and other bioactive compounds.",
    "parts": "Ageratum panamense is primarily used for its medicinal properties, and the plant's leaves and flowers are used to create traditional remedies. The leaves are rich in antioxidants and have anti-inflammatory properties, which are used to treat various health issues. In traditional medicine, Ageratum panamense is used to treat fever, cough, and respiratory problems. The plant's extracts are also used to treat skin conditions and wounds. Additionally, its leaves have been used in some cultures to treat digestive issues and reduce inflammation.",
    "intro": "Ageratum panamense, commonly known as Blue Mink or Mexican Bluebell, is a flowering plant species belonging to the Ageratum genus, native to Central America. The health benefits of Ageratum panamense include its potential anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties, which may aid in reducing inflammation and preventing infections. The bioactive constituents of this plant include flavonoids, terpenoids, and phenolic acids, which contribute to its therapeutic properties. Ageratum panamense is commonly used to make herbal preparations such as teas, infusions, and tinctures, which are traditionally used to treat various ailments, including fever, respiratory issues, and digestive problems."
